U.S. Treasury Department Schedule for Thursday, April 28

-- B y   V i n c e n t   D e l   G i u d i c e
-- 
2011-04-28T13:01:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/u-s-treasury-department-schedule-for-thursday-april-28.html
The following is a reformatted
version of the U.S. Treasury Department’s daily release on the
schedule for Secretary Timothy F. Geithner and other officials:  On Thursday, Secretary Geithner will travel to  Detroit ,
Michigan.  In the afternoon, the Secretary will visit Chrysler Group’s
Jefferson North Assembly Plant, where he will tour the facility
and discuss recent developments in the  auto industry  with
management, union leadership and workers. There will be a b-roll
opportunity of the tour for TV cameras and still photographers
only.  Later in the afternoon, the Secretary will meet with local
business leaders and participate in a moderated discussion
hosted by the Detroit Economic Club on the path forward for the
nation’s fiscal policy, strengthening U.S. competitiveness and
job creation, and the state of the economy. The Secretary’s
roundtable with local business leaders is closed press; his
remarks and moderated discussion before members of the Detroit
Economic Club is open press.  In the evening, the Secretary will return to Washington,
DC.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Del Giudice in  Washington  
 vdelgiudice@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net  